  "texts": [
    "Only one study explored students' learning strategies in an English task using video footage as stimuli in a virtual reality setting (Park, 2018).",
    "Thus, more than relying on text, images, or audio and video alone as stimuli is required, and more physiological and multimodal stimuli should be employed in future teaching and learning environments.",
    "The relationship between questioning strategy and research aim.",
    "The diagram presented here (Fig. 5) displays the questioning strategy and purpose of the study using the SR method, with the size of the bubbles representing the number of articles.",
    "Based on this information, our analysis aimed to explore whether the purpose of the study influenced questioning strategies."
  ]
}